        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:21PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coolville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parkersburg, Marietta, Belpre, Coolville, Vienna, Williamstown,
Washington, Boaz, Lubeck, North Hills, Little Hocking, Waverly,
Fleming, Blennerhassett, and Devola.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 173 and 186.
Interstate 77 in Ohio between mile markers 1 and 5, and near mile
marker 7.
Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 1 and 20.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
